# 6. 認めたくない

Kanade: (Tomorrow's the day I meet Mafuyu's mom...)
Kanade: (For Mafuyu's sake, I need to make a good argument...)
Kanade: (But...)
Message: <Because she's preparing for entrance exams.>
Message: <She is in pursuit of a different dream that doesn't involve music. If you truly are her friend, I'm sure you'd want her to focus on her studies.>
Message: <Even if there's a chance that it places her future in jeopardy?>
Kanade: (I solemnly believe that making songs together as N25 is having a positive effect on Mafuyu...)
Kanade: (But I can't speak for her dream or her future...)
Kanade: (What if her mom is right...? What if our work keeps her from studying the way she needs to and prevents her from achieving her dream...?)
Kanade: ...
Kanade: (I don't know what the right answer is...)
Kanade: But I can't mull this over forever...
Kanade: (Maybe I should try talking to Miku...)
Kanade: I wonder where Miku is...
Kanade: Oh, Miku. There you are.
Miku: Kanade...
Kanade: Are you okay? Did something—
???: But there's nothing I can do now...!
Kanade: Huh? That voice...
Kanade: Is that...KAITO? What's he doing...?
Mafuyu: I told her no...! I said that I didn't want to give up music!
Mafuyu: But...! She didn't care...
Mafuyu: What else can I do at this point...?!
KAITO: Shut up and calm down.
KAITO: If you're willing to give up after just that, then it's obviously not important enough.
KAITO: But that's not the case, is it? So quit lying to yourself.
Mafuyu: ...! I'm not lying to myself... I...!
KAITO: Fine, then do whatever you want.
KAITO: But mark my words. If you let things be, you'll never know who the “real” you is.
Mafuyu: ...!
KAITO: So, are you really okay with how things are...?
KAITO: You're here because you're not, right? Am I wrong?
Mafuyu: I just...
KAITO: If you believe that there's nothing else you can do, then let go of what you're feeling and get on with your life.
KAITO: If not...
KAITO: Then fight.
Mafuyu: Fight...? What do you mean...?
Mafuyu: My mom...? How am I supposed to do that...?
KAITO: You don't have time to be asking that...
KAITO: She's doing everything she can to destroy who you really are. How can you even think about showing her any mercy?
Mafuyu: Destroy who I am...?
Mafuyu: No...
Mafuyu: She cares about me. She's not trying to...
KAITO: Oh, come on. Open your eyes.
KAITO: You know exactly what she's trying to do. But you just keep—
Mafuyu: No... No...! Mom... She...!
Kanade: Wait, Mafuyu...
KAITO: Ugh. She ran away.
Rin: You went way too far there, KAITO.
Len: M-Mafuyu looked like she was in so much pain just now...
KAITO: You won't get through to her by sugarcoating what you say. I don't plan on babying her like the rest of you.
Miku: ...
Kanade: ...
Kanade: (Mafuyu really told her mom that she doesn't want to give up music...)
Kanade: (But it didn't work...)
Kanade: (I still don't know what I can say to help Mafuyu...)
Kanade: (I really don't know... But I need to say everything I can for her sake.)
Kanade: (Because at this rate, Mafuyu might...)
Kanade: (I'll say what I can tomorrow...)
Kanade: (I need to tell Mafuyu's mom just how much her daughter is suffering...)
Kanade: That's probably all I can do right now...
